The paper deals with geometric spanners, which are a fundamental topic in computational geometry and graph theory. The results involve point sets in the plane and their dilation, which are typical topics in computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also involves degree-based dilation and stretch factor, which are related to graph theory and discrete mathematics (cs.DS, cs.DM). The use of optimization techniques to find the worst-case dilation and stretch factor suggests the paper may also belong to the numerical analysis (cs.NA) and optimization (cs.SI) sub-categories.
